\section{Summary}\label{sec:summary}\nopagebreak[4]

Integration by parts and trigonometric substitution are invaluable techniques in calculus for solving complex integrals. Integration by parts simplifies integrals involving products of functions by transforming them into simpler forms. Trigonometric substitution is particularly effective for integrals involving radicals, leveraging trigonometric identities to simplify the integration process. Mastery of these techniques is essential for advanced mathematical problem-solving, providing a foundation for tackling challenging calculus problems.

