\needspace{6\baselineskip}
\section{Summary}\label{sec:summary}\nopagebreak[4]

Improper integrals extend the concept of definite integrals to situations involving infinite intervals or unbounded integrands. By using limits, we can evaluate these integrals and determine their convergence or divergence. Techniques such as the comparison test provide additional methods for analyzing integrals that are challenging to evaluate directly. Understanding improper integrals is essential for modeling real-world phenomena in engineering, physics, and other scientific fields.

