\item Simple interest accumulates linearly over time, adding a constant amount each period.
\item Compound interest grows exponentially due to the ``interest on interest'' effect.
\item The difference between simple and compound interest increases with longer time periods.
\item Future and present value calculations are essential for financial decision-making in engineering.
\item Cross-checking with financial calculators or software ensures accuracy.
\end{itemize}
\end{notebox}
