Using the simple interest formula for one year with annual compounding:
\begin{align*}
\text{Final Amount}_A &= \text{Principal} \times (1 + r_A) \\
\text{Final Amount}_A &= P \times (1 + 0.05) \\
\text{Final Amount}_A &= 1.05P
