\begin{solutionbox}
\textbf{Step 1: Calculate Effective Annual Rate for Option B}\\
Convert the nominal rate with quarterly compounding to an effective annual rate:
\begin{align*}
\text{EAR}_B &= \left(1 + \frac{0.068}{4}\right)^4 - 1 \\
\text{EAR}_B &= (1 + 0.017)^4 - 1 \\
\text{EAR}_B &= (1.017)^4 - 1 \\
