\begin{examplebox}{Example 7: EAIR Comparison (Annual vs. Semi-Annual)}
An engineering firm is considering two financing options for a new project. Option A offers a nominal interest rate of 7\% compounded annually, while Option B offers a nominal interest rate of 6.5\% compounded semi-annually. Which option results in a lower effective annual interest rate (EAIR)?

\textbf{Given:}
\begin{itemize}[noitemsep]
    \item Nominal interest rate for Option A: 7\% compounded annually
    \item Nominal interest rate for Option B: 6.5\% compounded semi-annually
\end{itemize}

\textbf{Required:} Determine the option with the lower effective annual interest rate.

\begin{figure}[H]
\centering
\begin{tabular}{lccc}
\toprule
\textbf{Option} & \textbf{Nominal Rate} & \textbf{Compounding} & \textbf{EAIR} \\
\midrule
A & 7\% & Annual ($n=1$) & 7.00\% \\
B & 6.5\% & Semi-annual ($n=2$) & 6.61\% \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\caption{Summary of interest rate calculations for both financing options.}
\end{figure}
\end{examplebox}

\begin{solutionbox}
\textbf{Step 1: Calculate EAIR for Option A}\\
For annual compounding, the effective rate equals the nominal rate:
\begin{align*}
\text{EAIR}_A &= \left(1 + \frac{0.07}{1}\right)^1 - 1 \\
\text{EAIR}_A &= (1 + 0.07)^1 - 1 \\
\text{EAIR}_A &= 0.07 = 7\%
\end{align*}

\textbf{Step 2: Calculate EAIR for Option B}\\
For semi-annual compounding with $n = 2$:
\begin{align*}
\text{EAIR}_B &= \left(1 + \frac{0.065}{2}\right)^2 - 1 \\
\text{EAIR}_B &= (1 + 0.0325)^2 - 1 \\
\text{EAIR}_B &= (1.0325)^2 - 1 \\
\text{EAIR}_B &= 1.0661 - 1 \\
\text{EAIR}_B &= 0.0661 = 6.61\%
\end{align*}

\textbf{Step 3: Compare EAIRs}\\
\begin{align*}
6.61\% &< 7\% \\
\text{EAIR}_B &< \text{EAIR}_A
\end{align*}
\[\boxed{\text{Option B: 6.61\% EAIR (lower cost)}}\]
\end{solutionbox}

\begin{notebox}
For financing decisions, the option with the lower EAIR results in lower interest costs. Despite Option A having annual compounding, Option B's lower nominal rate produces a lower effective rate, making it the preferred financing choice.
\end{notebox}
\end{samepage}

