\textbf{Exercise 1: Effective Annual Rate with Monthly Compounding}\\[0.5em]
\textbf{Step 1: Identify the parameters}\\
Nominal rate $r = 9\% = 0.09$, compounding periods $n = 12$ (monthly).

\textbf{Step 2: Apply the EAR formula}\\
\begin{align*}
\text{EAR} &= \left(1 + \frac{r}{n}\right)^n - 1 \\
\text{EAR} &= \left(1 + \frac{0.09}{12}\right)^{12} - 1 \\
\text{EAR} &= (1 + 0.0075)^{12} - 1 \\
\text{EAR} &= (1.0075)^{12} - 1 \\
