\begin{solutionbox}
\textbf{Step 1: Define Engineering Economics}\\
Engineering economics is the application of economic principles to engineering projects. It evaluates the economic viability of engineering solutions, focusing on cost, benefits, and overall economic impact.

\textbf{Step 2: Identify Primary Goal}\\
The primary goal is to maximize the economic value of engineering projects. This involves comparing costs and benefits to make informed decisions, ensuring resources are used efficiently to achieve optimal results.

\[\boxed{\text{The primary goal of engineering economics is to maximize the economic value of engineering projects by assessing costs and benefits to make informed decisions.}}\]
\end{solutionbox}
\begin{notebox}
Key Takeaways:
\begin{itemize}
  \item Engineering economics integrates economic and engineering principles.
  \item The primary goal is maximizing economic value.
  \item Informed decision-making is critical for project success.
\end{itemize}
\end{notebox}
