\textbf{Key Takeaways:}
\begin{itemize}[nosep]
\item The slope is a measure of how steep a line is
\item A positive slope indicates an upward trend from left to right
\item The slope formula uses differences of $y$ and $x$ coordinates
\end{itemize}
\textit{Verification:} Double-check calculations by ensuring the rise and run are correctly calculated and substituted back into the slope formula.
\end{notebox}
\end{samepage}

