\section*{Discussion Questions}
\nopagebreak[4]
\begin{samepage}
\begin{itemize}
  \item \textbf{Question:} How does the property of transitivity apply to inequalities and provide an example? \\
  \textbf{Answer Outline:}
  \begin{itemize}
    \item Transitivity means if $a < b$ and $b < c$, then $a < c$.
    \item Example: If 3 < 5 and 5 < 9, then 3 < 9.
    \item This property helps in solving compound inequalities.
  \end{itemize}

  \item \textbf{Question:} What are the challenges in graphing inequalities in two variables? \\
  \textbf{Answer Outline:}
  \begin{itemize}
    \item Identifying the boundary lines correctly.
    \item Determining the correct region to shade.
    \item Understanding how changes in inequality signs affect the graph.
